reviews.text: These cats are the bomb!  I've run a number of Chinese visa requests through them and every transaction has been timely and flawless.  If you need visa services from one of the Chicago consulates, this the place to go!

Tasty!  We were here on a weeknight and it was very quiet.  Beer battered Brussel sprouts are good, the  burgers were excellent.  They actually do medium rare correctly, so many other places just cook it to medium.

Delightful place. We are a couple and love to sit at the bar and eat and drink; bartenders are alert and competent, entrees and appetizers vary with the day, often unique and always tasty. 
Usually a good place for people watching, especially in the bar. Mostly couples ( straight, gay, women, men) seem to be fairly sophisticated and articulate. Bar has comfortable chairs and they have about twenty seats for high tops located close (but not too close) to the bar. Service is good, without being cloying. 
It ain’t cheap, but the pricing is more than fair. Decent, but not huge wine list (they’re more than glad to offer you a sample of any wine on their list), their spirits selection is fairly limited, but adequate and the bartenders seem to know how to make funky and obscure mixed drinks. 
Parking is generally available in the evening, but we do Lyft because we often find ourselves staying longer, and drinking more than we expected. 
I suppose I shouldn’t be writing such a glowing review, because we love this place just the way it is.
We just had sandwiches and figs, but everything was really good.

When my husband and I go to Tryst we typically eat at the bar and love it.  Service is great.   Fun vibe.  Food is constantly wonderful.  We love the burgers, the steak tips, the calamari, and the salmon.
Food was good, service was only okay. The maxx burger was good and portion was huge. Mushroom pasta was good, very rich.
This place is simple and awesome. As in filled with awe.

Won't address what I think about the institution but will talk only about the building, which is absolutely AMAZING. One of the most beautiful architectures in the city and in Israel, with a lot of natural light and a lot of symbols and meaning in how it was built. A gift for any photographer of architecture lover, views on the city and beautiful garden nearby as a bonus (also, worth checking the building from the outside and don't miss the courtyard!).
Free daily tours that are open to the general public take place at 11 a.m. in Hebrew and at 12 noon in English.
Accessibility: accessible parking, entrance to the building, toilets, water stations, voice guidance system, audio assistance system at the reception, directing signage, audio systems in courtrooms.
I believe everyone in Israel's supreme court should watch Lauren Southern's video on why feminism is an antynom for equality. Feminism is a movement for entitlements and supremacy.
They got a illuminati thing on top that aint cool. Flip the (bad) jews in here
Very impressive. Highly recommend the guided tour is about 1 hour long. Free.
What a pleasure to enjoy magnificent food! Went for Christmas dinner, and it was worth it. Service top notch. Anxious to return to order off the menu. Food was amazing and beautifully presented.

One of the worst dinning experience my husband and I have had! The food is ok, but over priced, and the service we had was the worst ever. We will not be returning there . We enjoyed the one in Princeton, but they obviously did not survive the move in our opinion.
Delicious and inventive food. Very pleasant service and an understanding for pacing a meal rather than turning tables.
Compliments to the chef. Excellence as expected. Very attentive wait staff.

Sonoma is the restaurant inside The Beechwood in Worcester. It's a standard restaurant for a nice hotel.  There isn't much stand-out about it good or bad. I really enjoyed their duck, which isn't easy to find in Worcester, and the cocktails were good.

Lovers of pizza always comes to Alberto's who is always on the rescue. Prices are just right and with varieties of flavors to choose from. It actually has a lot of branches all over Cebu City so you can grab get a pizza from any of these branches. A must see and try!
I always love the place and the pizza since the day this branch here opens. Love the staff that serves who were all friendly and keeps the place tidy. The place is very accessible. Must try!

Great pizza for a barkadahan feast..
Love the hawaian varity👍😘

This isn't a review of a particular Alberto's but their brand in general. After having lived in the Philippines over a year, I finally broke down and ordered pizza delivery, having low expectations.
This is definitely not pizza. And I'm not really sure it's food. The cheese is processed. The tomato sauce is a watered down form of ketchup. The dough is really more sad sponge than bread. It's a made to order food product that's essentially totally processed. 
I feel sorry for the person who created this company. He must've never tasted truly authentic pizza before he started making these impostor pizzas. By far the worst pizza I've had anywhere in the country.
Cheap yet one of the best tastes pizza in town 😍🍕

This is a very well laid out gallery. There are many early works, including many of prominent Aboriginal people and early pioneers. There are sculptures as well as paintings and sketches. Although I found much of it interesting, there are probably too many displays to make seeing the whole gallery a totally enjoyable experience. On the other hand, there is so much information about each of the items that it would be difficult to rush through too quickly.  It's great that our explorers, Australia's original people and business, sport and political figures are acknowledged with a portrait in the gallery. There is paid car parking below and a cafe.

Amazing! Spent hours here. So interesting and so much to see. We didn’t want to leave. On the day we visited it was quiet and relaxed and the perfect activity for a cold rainy day in Canberra. Will be back here again for sure.
A beautiful space. The collection is very diverse and incredibly high quality. The staff are friendly and helpful.

Mostly really good. 
Did have issues getting around with the pram and nappy bag as security was pretty tough. Recommend you take minimal on the day. Very basic parent room but it does the job. 
Echoed a bit (noticed when my newborn wouldn't stop farting lol). 
Well displayed artwork and pretty easy parking. Cafe was pretty good too.

NGA is a world class gallery, a large gallery comparable to those interstate and overseas. There are permanent and touring exhibitions, featuring a mix of contemporary and traditional art from Western and global artists. Something for everyone, suited to all ages and physical abilities. Good selection of indigenous art, and well curated selection of Australian art generally.

Well restored national theater of Athens. Two venues inside the same building, the old historic one, beautifully kept, and a smaller space for more experimental theater. Always top level theater performances of the National Theater. You just can't go wrong by attending a theater performances there. Always too quality level word, and totally not staid!!!

My favorite theater in Athens. The building is amazing and the time you spend there always with hight quality. The area is not that safe but it worth it. Take the metro and choose omonia metro station. It is like 2’ walking from there. Do not hesitate to take an outside photo and of course to enjoy any event, just to realize the unique feeling. Sometimes there are offers on the tickets.
Such a superb place to be. Great theatrical plays on the stage, historical building with modern commodities - stage, lights, new wing!
A great theater for great plays, always enjoyed when I visit
Theater always decent but sometimes excellent

Food was excellent. I ate way too much. Don't fill up on the salad bar or sides. They are really quick to come around with the meats. Tables are close together but we were next to a couple of nice ladies so it didn't bother us. Our waiter was super nice.

Love this place. Staff is excellent. A bit pricey... You get what you pay for. Sign up on their web site and you can receive coupons/discounts. Best steak house in Baltimore by far. A lot of variety of meats and great place to go with friends and family. I had an amazing time at Fogo. The staff is friendly, the food is amazing and it’s an all around great experience. MUST GO!!!

I love Fogo de Chão, either Baltimore or D.C. are great. You might want to take with you a list of the meat cuts so you can make sure you tried them all after your visit. In some cases, you end up eating the same cut several times and you don't get to try other cuts. Never had a cold peace of steak. Servers are awesome, salad bar is great. The best Brazilian steakhouse IMO.

Top notch, napkins down, a good time! My friend and I went to Fogo De . The experience was great! the staff was responsive, quick to meet needs, and we even got a complimentary chees cake to celebrate. Would diffidently go back to celebrate more occasions. I had an amazing time at Fogo. The staff is friendly, the food is amazing and it’s an all around great experience. MUST GO!!!

5 star food, 5 star service. The staff was amazing, quick and ready to go. The self serve bar was really good but the meats, they were all out of this world. The service manager is a great guy, he spent some time talking with the table about all the different things they had, we missed one somehow. He had it brought out to us to try. That’s service you just can’t get anywhere else. We will be going back. It’s worth the trip if you can do it. Be ready to tap out however. The meat doesn’t stop coming unless you make sure the card is on the red. The hard part is, it’s all good. You don’t want to stop.

Park is lovely. And amazing in New York City terms. Why do I say that? Since this park in Brooklyn is something you go to for fun day. Many other town it would be just another park. Evening is when everybody comes here. So try mornings...
Love this park, grew up learning how to bike ride, play football, ice skate, sledding. Went on my first carousel ride. Had my best birthday parties. Exploring and "getting lost" is always fun.

Awesome alternative if you get tired of Central Park. Prospect Park is a lot less city-influenced, so you feel nature more here. It’s also less crowded, but still with a beautiful pond/lake and giant meadow. It’s great!

It’s one of the most calm and nice places to relax, from the late afternoon to 1 AM. The 5 stars only applies to after 6:30 PM... when it’s more crowded I’d still give it a 4 star. It’s really worth visiting for a relaxation, but not really as a tourist. Except he needs a calm place for a break. Perfect for a meeting, date, etc
Went there for the Smorgasburg food event, it was great. The park is large and very nice. Plenty of open areas and sports fields. Great place for a picnic!
Had plenty of Thai food over the years but I have to say mai thai is absolutely amazing. So authentic, so much flavour and cooked to perfection. Definitely be back. Wayne from South Wales 👍
It was delicious, we had the set meal for two, just about managed to eat it all. The waitress was friendly and helpful and the service was really good.

I'm really sad to say our visit to Mai Thia was very disappointing. We had a set meal. Our starters we lovely but we had a 'soup' and main dishes were basically tasteless except for the beef dish which had an overpowering aniseed flavour. Lemongrass had been chopped into the dishes therefore every mouthful you had, you were picking the hard lemongrass out. I did mention to the waitress this wasn't to my liking but she said that's what Thia food is like! The dessert was banana fritters, and like the starter thus was nice. I love Thia food and have had the pleasure of eating in a few Thia restusrants but Mai Thia really has a different take on This food!! If this was your first experience of Thia food, I don't think you would want to eat Thia again.
Wonderful food and service, plus free parking outside.
Lovely authentic Thai restaurant. Friendly staff, generous portions, great food. Nice laid-back vibe -- a lovely neighbourhood restaurant.

It was a great place,  the atmosphere,  the location,  the service. The total package was so good that makes you happy by the end of the day and think of returning. Alas with the sad news surfacing,  I hope the place makes a come back.
Nice food and location on the Nile

I love this place. It has the perfect view by the Nile especially if you are lucky enough to have a first row table. The food is amazing with a nice set of varieties. It is a suitable place for gatherings and events and in the summer it is advised to go by sunset and in winter the place would be great at noon for a brunch or lunch.
A really beautiful place to spend an evening by the nile

Nice & comfortable friendly place.
And, prices are reasonable relative to the high quality they introduce.
Moreover it has an amazing view for Nile river.
Pretty little area in the city
Fantastic place to honor our veterans!

The half smoke is the way to go here. Wish the bun was of better quality. The half smoke has a nice crunch and excellent flavor. The chili is good too, but being from Southern California I prefer the chili from a different local place. Don't get me wrong, it is good here. Got the spicy chili by accident on our chili fries and it's way too spicy for me and I like medium spicy heat.

Had heard about Ben's and did it deliver! Hot dog and sausage were spot on. Wonderful crunch to the sausage/hot dog. Chili had wonderful flavor and the fries hot and fresh.  Service was warm, friendly and quick. Awesome place for a quick bite!
Great food and quick service! The chili is always amazing and the staff is always making sure you have the best time possible. This place is a must go whenever in the area!
I don't know if you have to visit the orginal Ben's Chili Bowl or this is what they all are like, but I had a bad experience. Chili has no flavor, expensive ($1 for "cheese"), and dirty.
I'm coming back great food and people! I was sick the chili made me well.
Best
Mooi historisch pand aan de markt. Rondleidingen door het pand worden gegeven door Kring Vrienden van 's-Hertogenbosch.  Te boeken via dagjedenbosch.com. Een aanrader.
Beetje ouderwets.

In dit pand is onder andere de Ombudsman van de gemeente 's-Hertogenbosch gevestigd.
Deze Ombudsman is vaak de laatste strohalm die mensen hebben.
Echter is deze commissie niet van fouten verschoond, fouten die zij zelf toegegeven hebben.

Toch weerhouden die fouten hen er niet van om 'over lijken te gaan' en medewerkers van de gemeente die hun boekje te buiten gaan een handje boven het hoofd te blijven houden ! 

Wat in een onprofessionele, bijna corrupte en incompetente organisatie resulteert.
Men zal zich hier uiteraard 'niet in herkennen' maar dat is altijd het standaard rookgordijn dat snel opgetrokken wordt om zaken binnenkamers te houden.

When you want a delicious fresh made to order burger this is the place to go.  Great burgers ,fresh buns , and many delicious  toppings.  Food is  consistantly good and service is fast and friendly. I like when you order fries they don't skimp on the amount and always throw  extra into the bag.  Fries are cut fresh and delicious.  Clean restaurant with nice seating.  Free peanuts to munch on while you wait.  Food is delicious .  Love it.

This Five Guys was amazing. I was able to order online so I only waited a few minutes.  They gave me a free soft drink while I waited.  I received an amazing burger, plenty of perfect very hot fries.  Clean, quick and awesome service.

Always a good experience. Staff is pleasant (and they were even singing along to the music, which was fun) and the restaurant is always clean. Coke machine was out of quite a few flavor cartridges, but this was the first time that happened.

The food is good but I always thought it is expensive for what you get. 
We got 2 small cokes, small French fries, 1 bacon cheese burger (double patty) and 1 cheese burger (single) .... All for the bargain price of $27.30! Plus a wonderfully cozy atmosphere.
This place was always so clean & staff was so friendly. Anyone else notice the un-cleanliness or the attitudes between the pm manger & staff :(  we will not be returning!

St. John’sChurch is one of the oldest medieval architectural monuments in Latvia. Church was built in the beginning of 13th century during the Christianization of Baltic’s for the purposes of the Livonian Holy Order because residence of the order was located in Cēsis; therefore Cēsis became one of the most important German power centers in the Baltic’s from 1237 up to 1561

Pretty, very old, church with a terrifying (fun) option to tour the bell tower. The church is pretty, but let's be honest - all churches from that era are. For mere 2€ you can take your life in your hands and climb the stairs of the ~65m bell tower for a view. Most of the thrill comes from navigating the near-black steep staircase on your way up. Still, I enjoyed it.
A good place

The church facade still awaits restoration, but the community seems to be very active. The guide, a senior lady, is very vigorous, helpful and gave lots of information, as did the exhibitions inside. The tombs of the Masters of the Livonian Order and the stained glass with the Latvian coat of arms, which was miraculosly preserved by the pastor during the Soviet time are impressive.
Nice church, nothing special.

We go here a few times a year.  Our go to for special occasions.  We have never been disappointed.   Always fantastic meal, outstanding service and great experience.   Hopefully this was a one time occurrence.  6 people, 5 prime ribs ordered.  Only one was cooked correctly.  They seemed to be reheated or older roasted ribs.  4 were ordered M-MR and we're delivered well done, exempt from any red at all.  They did try to make it right by bringing a new cut.  I just expect it right the first time and that everyone should eat together.  Timing was off.  Disappointed this time.

Love the atmosphere!  The food is typically consistent and service is always impeccable.  This time I ordered the clams and there was a lot of shell in every one of them, I was barely offered an apology for it.  I expect more from the Prime Rib.

This is not the place to go if you're on a budget. However, if you want to splurge, or you have the $$$$ to spend the night out, go for it. I had the delicious crab cakes, potatoes au gratin, potato skins, and hot fudge sundae for desert. Attentive waiters, free valet parking, piano music, low-volume atmosphere. I enjoyed my visit.

My wife and I were in visiting for the weekend . Whenever we travel we always try to find a nice restaurant to eat steak / seafood . After reading reviews we settled in on this place . I’m glad we did , everything was outstanding ! I had the prime rib and my wife had flounder stuffed with crab which she believes was the best she has ever had . There house salad was delicious and the creamed spinach did not disappoint . I tried the the potato skins with horseradish add on as a previous reviewer had mentioned . Phenomenal ! The oyster Rockefeller was also great . I liked there shrimp cocktail which I get just about anywhere I get a chance . This was the best food we had while in Baltimore . If I lived here I would be a regular there . I thought the food was reasonably priced for the quality of what you get . If I had to pick out any negative at all it would be the size of restaurant . It’s close quarters eating . Although for that food I would eat in the bathroom 😁.

We went for restaurant week. The prime rib was an extra surcharge ($5), which was not posted on the Baltimore restaurant week site. That was a unwanted surprise. Otherwise, service was slow and relaxed, which I liked. Food was good, but I would not pay full price for the meal if it wasn't on special this week. Dessert was excellent. Overall, it was a very good experience.
